Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class SetInclusionExclusionPredicateEvaluator.SetInclusionExclusionInstructions<T>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.SetInclusionExclusionPredicateEvaluator.SetInclusionExclusionInstructions<T>
Enclosing class:
SetInclusionExclusionPredicateEvaluator
public static class SetInclusionExclusionPredicateEvaluator.SetInclusionExclusionInstructions<T>
extends java.lang.Object
Often (e.g. with selecting which instruments will participate in a backtest) we need to have rules such as 'include A, B, C; exclude everything else 'exclude D, E, F; include everything else 'include A, B, C; exclude D, E, F; for everything else, use your own rules' (most general case) This class represents all these cases. It is intentionally not a top-level class. This way, I don't need to expose its data.
